<tr>
<td height=82></td>
<td width=418 height=82 valign=top align=left>

<p align=left><font face="Arial" color=#800080 size=2>This 1998 photo shows the northbound Bronx River Parkway in Scarsdale. When this section opened in 1925, there was no divider to separate the opposing traffic lanes. The median guardrail was added later under the leadership of Robert Moses. (Photo by Steve Anderson.)<br></font>
</td>
<td></td>
