<p align=left><font face="Arial" color=#800080 size=2>LEFT: This 1922 photo shows the Bronx River Parkway in the area of the Woodlawn Metro-North railroad station. RIGHT: This 1928 photo shows the Bronx River Parkway at the Ardsley Road overpass in Scarsdale. Note the undivided four-lane design of the original roadway. (Photos from Westchester County archives, call numbers &#35;A-0321-(2)F-PH95 and &#35;A-0321-(2)F-PH107.) </font><font face="Times New Roman" size=3><br></font>
