<td height=64></td>
<td width=549 height=64 valign=top align=left>

<p align=left><font face="Arial" color=#800080 size=2>This 1998 photo shows the northbound Bronx River Parkway just south of EXIT 6 (US 1 / Boston Post Road) in the Bronx. The southerly extension of the parkway into the Bronx reflected the design standards of the immediate post-World War II era, such as higher design speeds and median separation. (Photo by Steve Anderson.) <br></font>
</td>
<td></td>
